Skyscraper becomes a Hong Kong landmark
2012-06-26 08:14:22 GMT
The 118-floor International Commerce Center (ICC) is one of the world's top 10 tallest buildings, in Hong Kong's Kowloon.ICC is 490 meters tall and opened in May 2011. Tourists can enjoy the view from the Sky100 lounge on the 100th floor, which is the only site with a 360-degree view of Hong Kong. The Ritz-Carlton Hotel occupies floors 102 to 118 inside the ICC, becoming the world's highest hotel.
